December 20 at 7:00 PM ·

“You have to see failure as the beginning and the middle, but never entertain it as an end.”
-Jessica Herrin, founder and CEO of Stella & Dot

This is the main mantra of a successful entrepreneur. He suffers with a lot of issues at the start , but he finds his way through and in the end, comes out on top with flying colours. That is the nature of a hard working businessman.
Kalyani Government Engineering College Entrepreneurship Cell organises an event which is comprised of t...hree sessions including a pitching workshop guided by Mr. Ankan Chattopadhyay and Mr. Bikash Prajapti, Joint Secretaries of KGEC E-cell. Although the main attraction of the event is the session on Finance where Prof. Biswanath Chakraborty, faculty of Mechanical Engineering department, will share his opinions on the above mentioned topic.
There is also an interactive session to be held where students with their budding entrepreneurial mind, will be guided by Mr. Sourav Bhattacharya, CEO and Co-founder of Originals, and Mr. Bikash Prajapti, Co-founder of Originals, on whether College is the right time to start up.

So guys, it is going to be an highly exciting and eventful day tomorrow. Hope you all will participate in it and gather valuable insights on their future entrepreneurial career. See you there....

KGEC E-Cell
December 15 at 9:00 AM ·

Who does the cashier at the nearby mall, feed your data to.💡Let's look at Point of Sale (POS) today, and where and how your data is used, to ease our shopping experience everyday. 😎

The POS is the place (physical or virtual) in a shop (brick-mortar or online) where a product is passed from the seller to the customer. 🤑

The software running at the respective pos system, stores and uses your information to generate your bill. Additionally depending on the size and type of shop,... this information may be stored at some central repository, for future reference too.🌎

The personal information like name, contact number, mail, address may then be used for additional promotional advertisement. 😑

👉 𝐹𝑜𝑙𝑙𝑜𝑤 𝑜𝑢𝑟 𝑝𝑎𝑔𝑒𝑠 𝑎𝑡 𝐹𝑎𝑐𝑒𝑏𝑜𝑜𝑘 𝑎𝑛𝑑 𝐼𝑛𝑠𝑡𝑎𝑔𝑟𝑎𝑚.

With the good news of our selection for the final round of NEC at IIT Bombay, its time for us to pull up our socks and make our presence felt more vehemently. As a task pertaining to the same, we are conducting this survey.

Apart from rigorous class assessments, the only thing that students are tired of is getting their regular fees and hostel bills paid at counters. The ICICI bank wants to bring a more efficient way of the transaction to help the students pay their bills wit...h the most comfort and ease. The link below will fetch you to a short survey that will help to generate the insights of how the ongoing systems work and the possible betterment of it.

KGEC E-Cell
December 8 at 9:00 AM ·

Recently corporates have been having a hard time, proving how they are not a monopoly and indeed just a small fish in a big pond. Let's take a look at #Monopolies and when does a corporate qualify to be called one. 😎

A monopoly refers to a company when its product offerings dominate one sector or industry.😳 Considered as an extreme result of free-market capitalism and often used to describe an entity that has total or near-total control of a market. ⚡

Ruthless business practi...ces, copyrights and patents, assistance from the government, access to scarce resources, or exceptional products and services are some ways to create one. 😱
